<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-11-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-11-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="440" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d440">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Reid</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-11-15"><hi rend="italic">November 15,
                                    1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Reid reports that Lord Lansdowne has promised him that he will
                            immediately communicate with the colonial department and do everything
                            possible.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>